reviewText:
It is a real short game, but still funny as it's seems.

Pros:
- Incredibly charismatic characters (especially the two main: Bwanga and Kito);
- Good voice acting;
- Really nice art (-African masks/culture inspiration; -Noir movies atmosphere; -Reggae/Jazz Music; -Jamaican accent)
- Amazing soundtrack;
- Bwanga's commentaries about things;
- Crazy and absurd problem solutions;

Cons:
- Sometimes, Bwanga walking through scenarios seems to be too slow;
- Some crazy and absurd solutions may be way too much;
- The chinese cook;
- I understand that this is just a chapter, but the gameplay is really, really short for it's price (can finish in 2hrs);

Conclusion:
This is a great game to get start into the point-and-click genre. Also good for kids, and definitly deserves a place in Library for it's cultural value.

